Accountable_Organization_Office: Trade and Development Agency
Award_Title: Live Wire Maintenance And Repair Reverse Trade Mission
Award_Description: This Reverse Trade Mission ('RTM') is supporting the planned establishment of Live Wire Maintenance and Repair ('LWMR') in Turkey. The objective of this RTM is to familiarize up to fifteen high-ranking officials from Turkey's energy sector with advanced U.S. technologies, best practices and techniques, as well as regulations for LWMR operations. This would then enable the Turkish delegates to have a better framework to implement a nationwide LWMR strategy in Turkey.

Accountable_Organization_Office: Trade and Development Agency
Award_Title: Middle East Technical University (METU) Smart Campus Project Technical Assistance
Award_Description: USTDA is funding this technical assistance (TA) to support the Middle East Technical University (METU) in developing a smart and sustainable campus. The TA will explore the benefits of applying advanced technology solutions to enhance the areas of smart energy, smart transportation, smart water management, smart buildings and Information and Communication Technology ('ICT'), management and control systems. In addition to the development of detailed sector strategies, the TA will provide technical, operational and financial guidance to serve as a roadmap for implementing the METU Smart Campus Project. Ultimately, the goal of the smart campus project is to enable METU to determine how to best achieve integration of campus infrastructure and services through an integrated, centrally managed and operated project.
Award_Transaction_DAC_Purpose_Code_Name: Multisector education/training
Treasury_Account_Title: Trade and Development Agency, Funds Appropriated to the President

Extending_Organization_Office: U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service-International Affairs
Accountable_Organization_Office: U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service-International Affairs
Award_Title: Developing A Conservation Project To Address Sea Turtle Bycatch Mortality In Mediterranean Coast Of Turkey
Award_Description: The purpose of this project is to develop a sea turtle conservation program to address fisheries bycatch issues near the main loggerhead nesting beaches in Turkey.  Activities will include: (1) placing two on board observers on fishing boats to gather information on fishing operations, gear and sea turtle captures on the far eastern and western Turkish Mediterranean coast; (2) deploying GPS tracking devices with volunteer fisherman to determine main fishing areas and “hotspots”; (3) testing LED lights as bycatch reduction measures; (4) implementing awareness and outreach campaign for safe release and handling of turtles accidently captured in net, trawl or long line fisheries and new techniques to reduce captures; and (5) in water netting surveys to assess sea turtle population structure on foraging grounds.
Award_Transaction_DAC_Purpose_Code_Name: Bio-diversity
Treasury_Account_Title: Multinational Species Conservation Fund, United States Fish and Wildlife Service

Accountable_Organization_Office: Trade and Development Agency
Award_Title: Air Simulation For The New Istanbul Airport Technical Assistance
Award_Description: This technical assistance grant is partially funding and supporting the design of the optimal airspace, runway approaches and air traffic control operating procedures for the New Istanbul Airport. The New Istanbul Airport is scheduled to open in 2018 and when completed in 2024, it will be one of the largest in the world, hosting 150 million passengers annually on flights to more than 350 destinations. Accordingly, IGA Havalimani Isletmesi A.S. (IGA), the concessionaire that will operate the airport for 25-years, is seeking technical assistance to ensure that the airspace operates at sufficient capacity to meet the anticipated traffic demand on the opening day in 2018.
Award_Transaction_DAC_Purpose_Code_Name: Transport policy and administrative management
Treasury_Account_Title: Trade and Development Agency, Funds Appropriated to the President

Extending_Organization_Office: U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service-International Affairs
Accountable_Organization_Office: U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service-International Affairs
Award_Title: Developing A Conservation Project To Address Sea Turtle Bycatch Mortality In Mediterranean Coast Of Turkey
Award_Description: The purpose of this project is to develop a sea turtle conservation program to address fisheries bycatch issues near the main loggerhead nesting beaches in Turkey.  Activities will include: (1) placing two on board observers on fishing boats to gather information on fishing operations, gear and sea turtle captures on the far eastern and western Turkish Mediterranean coast; (2) deploying GPS tracking devices with volunteer fisherman to determine main fishing areas and “hotspots”; (3) testing LED lights as bycatch reduction measures; (4) implementing awareness and outreach campaign for safe release and handling of turtles accidently captured in net, trawl or long line fisheries and new techniques to reduce captures; and (5) in water netting surveys to assess sea turtle population structure on foraging grounds.
Award_Transaction_DAC_Purpose_Code_Name: Bio-diversity
Treasury_Account_Title: Multinational Species Conservation Fund, United States Fish and Wildlife Service
